HEADWORD: Aphanite
<hw>Aph"a*nite</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
invisible; <grk>'a</grk> priv. + <?/ to appear.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A very compact, dark-colored rock, consisting of hornblende, or
pyroxene, and feldspar, but neither of them in perceptible
grains.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

